transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop.
In today's video we are introducing the feature using which admins can now manage the default properties of block PDFs from the admin panel itself.
In version 11.0, the Manage Properties screen for adding properties as designed to have to new tabs.
First custom properties which are offered by the On Print Shop platform and 2nd default properties which are offered by Abode Acrobat.
This we have incorporated with our platform to ease the editing process for the admins.
So let us walk you through the steps to manage some of these default properties.
From the admin panel, go to your admin panel, navigate to the Templates section and click on the PDF block templates.
From the template list, select the PDF block template for which you want to change some properties.
Here we are selecting this template to change the position or alignment of the designation block and change the font style and color.
From the Action drop down menu, click on Manage Blocks.
On the Manage Blocks screen you will find all the text and image blocks added to the template.
As you can see in the preview, the alignment of the designation block is on the right side and we need to align it with the other blocks.
Along with that, we need to modify the font and color of the text blocks.
So click on the Manage Properties link against the designation block and on the next screen click on the Add button.
Here you can see that the screen now has two tabs.
All the previous properties are moved to the Custom properties and the Default Properties tab is added with these five properties.
To change the alignment of the designation block, select Object Fitting and then Other options will appear.
The system will detect and display the default options in the fields.
To change the alignment, enter zero in the Position X field and click on Save and Back.
Now from the drop down, select Full Name and then click on the Add button.
Move to the Default Properties tab and select the Font property.
Here you can see that the font is Robito Bold and the style is Bold Italic.
Let's change the style to Normal.
Change the font size to 10 and click on Save.
Let's also change the color for the Full name block.
For this select Color property.
Enter the CMYK code for another color and click on Save and back.
Exit the Manage Properties screen.
Save all the details made once again and finally click on the Update Preview button to apply the changes to the template.
Here you can verify that the alignment of the designation block has now changed from right to left, the font style for the full name has changed to normal and the color has also changed.

Similarly, you can also manage other given properties from the admin panel, for which you had to 1st download the file from OPS panel, upload it in Acrobat, make changes, and then again upload it in the admin panel.
This was all about the new default properties added to the block PDF templates.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
